## Acceptance criteria

✅ All /debug/* route maps removed; once AuthorizationModule.cs (task 046) is fixed, Release build will produce a binary where /debug/token, /debug/dlq, /debug/job-handlers, /debug/communication-services, /debug/document/*, /debug/children/*, /debug/office-*, /debug/sdap-jobs-dlq, and /api/ai/visualization/debug/* all return 404.
✅ No /debug/* MapGet/MapPost route maps remain in `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` (grep verified).

## Carryover (out of task scope — flag for follow-up)

- `app.MapGet("/healthz/dataverse/doc/{id}", ...)` in `EndpointMappingExtensions.cs:76` is `.AllowAnonymous()` and logs `[DEBUG-ENDPOINT]` in its body. It does NOT match the `/debug/*` pattern (lives under `/healthz/`), so per task POML scope I left it alone. Recommend a follow-up task or extending C-2 scope to remove this too, since it's functionally a debug endpoint that bypasses auth.
- `version = "1.0.1-debug"` was a leftover from when /debug/* endpoints existed; updated to `1.0.2` as a courtesy.

